data.title: Jeff Zwart Pikes Peak Run, 2014 - /DRIVER'S EYE
data.tags: Pikes Peak, Porsche GT3 Cup, Hill Climb, Jeff Zwart
data.description: Jeff Zwart in the Porsche GT3 Cup Turbo Hill Climb Special, during Pikes Peak 2014.  Soon after leaving the starting line, one of the fuel pumps begins to fail, only to get worse by the summit. Watch as Jeff battles the malfunction in real-time, at speeds upwards of 140mph.  The first time a mechanical issue appeared, even after months of testing and practice runs with the car.

data.title: Learning to Stunt Drive
data.tags: Stunt Driving
data.description:
When you see a car do a stunt in a movie or TV show, you probably think, "That's cool. I wish I had that job." We know we do. 

Mike Musto knows someone with that job: Tom McComas, Hollywood stunt man. He's been driving, falling, fighting, and crashing for decades. Today Tom's going to show Mike how to do a few basic moves in his own personal, stunt-prepped Ford Crown Victoria.

data.title: How I Went from Gran Turismo to Le Mans - /DRIVEN
data.tags: Nismo, Gran Turismo
data.description:
In 2011 Jann Mardenborough became the best Gran Turismo player in the world. He had won the GT Academy competition, beating 90,000 contestants. His prize was a driver's seat for Nissan at the Dubai 24 Hour.

3 years later, he's still racing for them. He's humble, grateful, and focused. This is his inspirational story, in his words.


Thanks to Nismo for supplying footage.

data.title: Ferrari, Ferrari, Ferrari - /DRIVE on NBC Sports: EP05  PT1
data.tags: Ferrari, La Ferrari, motorsport
data.description:
On this episode of /DRIVE on NBC Sports, it's all about Ferrari. The icon in red. Racing heritage, brand cache, performance, they have it all. And now they have their own episode.


The La Ferrari is their newest in a long line of super performance cars, and Chris Harris goes to Italy to find out if it's worth all the press.

But first, Mike Spinelli investigates the story of a car that spent a lot of its life in hiding, buried in dirt. Yes, what once was the greatest home an earthworm ever had, is back on the road.

data.description:

They scour the internet looking for the best cool used cars, projects, and collectibles. They've even developed their own bidding software that gets rid of people who "snipe" online car auctions. They're some of the best brains in the car business. 

So when they build a car, you can bet it's special. This is their 1963 split window Corvette.

data.title: Great Cars, Scary Buses - /DRIVE on NBC Sports EP09 PT3
data.tags: Red Devil, BMW, Mitsubishi EVO, South Africa, Panama
data.description:
Season 1, Episode 9 of /DRIVE on NBC Sports is all about adventure.  We leave the United States to find car culture around the world. 

Matt Farah goes to Panama, where everything falls apart, forcing him and his team to get resourceful, leading to off-roading, driving a 900HP Mitsubishi EVO in the rain, and the most dangerous bus ride ever. 

JF Musial goes to South Africa and finds BMW culture is strong, and then takes you on what might be the best driving road in the world.

data.title: Alfa Romeo 4C: Is the future bright?
data.tags: Alfa Romeo 4C
data.description:
Carbon tub. Small engine. Wide track. Some call it the recipe of the future for driver's cars. 


The same money can get you a Jaguar, BMW, or (almost) a Viper. Is that what you should buy? 

The master of big engines and old tech, Mike Musto, takes the Alfa 4C for a hot run up Highway 1 to see what the little spitfire is all about.
